oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Sgt. Julius S. Burchfield, Co. B, 117th Inf. Regt., 30th Div., traveled over to Europe on this Liberty Ship. From Rasar, Tennessee, he enlisted as a private in June 1917, was promoted to corporal in October 1917, then to sergeant in October 1918. He served overseas from May 11, 1918 until March 27, 1919.
